     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <head>To the Reader.</head>
   <l>BEyond the reach of vulgar intellect,</l>
   <l>Inbred by Nature, but refin'd by Art,</l>
   <l>Doth wisdomes <hi>Heyre</hi> this monument erect,</l>
   <l>Grace't with what ere the <hi>Graces</hi> can impart.</l>
   <l>Here, Wits not soild with looser blandishment.</l>
   <l>The <hi>Subiect</hi> pure, abstruse, and worthy paine,</l>
   <l>Annatomizing civill goverment,</l>
   <l>And, of the <hi>Soule</hi> what Reason can attaine.</l>
   <l>The many <hi>sweetes</hi> herein contained be,</l>
   <l>Epitomiz'd, would aske too large Narration</l>
   <l>To be compris'd within this narrow station.</l>
   <l>Reade then the <hi>VVorke</hi>: when, if thou canst not see</l>
   <l>Th'infolded flame; be rapt with admiration,</l>
   <l>But censure not: for, <hi>Owles</hi> haue bleared eies,</l>
   <l>Dazled with every <hi>Starre</hi> that doth arise.</l>
</div>
